In this update:
[1] Belgium
[2] France

******
[1] Belgium
Date: Fri 8 Dec 2017
Source: Belgium's Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain (FAVV-AFSCA) press release [Dutch, transl, edited]
http://www.favv.be/persberichten/2017/2017-12-08.asp


The 4th and 5th foci of bovine tuberculosis have been confirmed on [Wed 29 Nov and Fri 1 Dec 2017].

Focus 4 is a "beef cattle fattening establishment, in a cattle trader's exporting facility, West Flanders, including some 200 cattle.

Focus 5 is a "beef cattle fattening establishment, Limburg, with about 40 cattle.

The foci 2 to 5 have all been discovered in the context of the epidemiological investigation that had been started after the confirmation of the 1st focus in Antwerp province, at the end of Jul 2017. The fact that 2 of the infection foci were active in livestock trade has led to the incorporation of many establishments in the epidemiological investigation.

