******
[2] France
Date: Tue 5 Dec 2017 11:29
Source: Plateforme-esa (Epidemiological Surveillance Resource Center for Animal Health, France) [French, transl, edited]
https://www.plateforme-esa.fr/article/campagne-de-prophylaxie-2017-2018-contre-la-tuberculose-bovine-intensification-du-recours-a


Between Jan and Sep 2017, 84 outbreaks of tuberculosis were detected on the national territory, of which 86 percent in the Nouvelle-Aquitaine region. Despite many years of struggle and increased surveillance, infected areas in this region tend to grow and the number of outbreaks to increase.

The persistence of the disease in these areas undermines the maintenance of France's free status and jeopardizes the eradication of tuberculosis, which remain the priority objectives reaffirmed several times in Cnopsav , most recently on [Thu 12 Oct 2017].

Improving the health situation of the territory involves both strengthening surveillance and biosecurity measures. The national action plan against bovine tuberculosis is therefore under revision for the period 2017-2022.

With regard to surveillance, the exchanges with the actors in the field highlighted the difficulties to carry out the intra-dermal tuberculinations according to the [2015 guidelines] concerning the technical provisions relating to the detection of bovine tuberculosis on live animals.

These difficulties are in the 1st place practical, given the, at times, deficient restraint of the examined animals [when a single intradermal tuberculination, SDI, is applied, leading to non-specific results at a concerning rate].

The comparative intra-dermotuberculin test, CDI, has the advantage of increasing sensitivity without unduly degrading specificity.

The use of IDC has been made mandatory for all cattle over 24 months of herds subject to prophylaxis in the Dordogne, as well as for the other departments of New Aquitaine and for the Occitan region, for livestock classified at risk or located in the defined risk zones within the meaning of the ministerial decree of 7 Dec, 2016.

In order to disseminate good practice in implementing this demanding practice, the Ministry of Agriculture and Food has produced 2 videos for breeders and veterinarians (in French):

"Bovine tuberculosis: screening and diagnosis" at https://www.plateforme-esa.fr/tuberculose-bovine-depistage-et-diagnostic.

"Use and maintenance of the syringe lintock" at https://www.plateforme-esa.fr/utilisation-et-entretien-de-la-seringue-a-tuberculiner-mc-lintock.

These 2 videos are complemented by an information brochure on the implementation of the CDI, intended to be widely distributed.(In French, at https://tinyurl.com/ybw7ale8).

Authored by:
Fabrice Chevalier, Lisa Cavalry and Anne Bronner. Ministry of Agriculture and Food, General Directorate of Food, Bureau of Animal Health, Paris, France

